The Apple iPad, on the other hand, is equipped with Apple's custom designed A6X processor, which is also an ARM processor, but this dual-core processor is supplemented with only four graphics cores. While it's tempting to read something into the raw specs of the processors, it's worth noting that both tablets have tailored the hardware and software to work together, and Windows RT is a different beast than Apple's iOS.
